02:42.512 --> 02:43.930
♪ Men. ♪

02:44.923 --> 02:46.606
When's your mom
getting in?

02:46.608 --> 02:47.941
Any time now.

02:47.943 --> 02:49.476
She's on her way
up from San Diego.

02:49.478 --> 02:51.478
Oh, hey, is Jake's room ready?

02:51.480 --> 02:52.813
I did what I could.

02:52.815 --> 02:55.198
It still has kind of
a teenage stink to it.

02:55.200 --> 02:58.068
Maybe I should put her
in Alan's room.

02:58.070 --> 03:00.704
Oh, no, that smells
like failure and foot powder.

03:01.906 --> 03:03.824
Is that mistletoe?

03:03.826 --> 03:04.908
Yes.

03:04.910 --> 03:06.626
Well, bring it, Santa.

03:07.912 --> 03:10.747
Oh, merry Christmas to me.

03:10.749 --> 03:14.334
You know they make belt
buckles with mistletoe on 'em?

03:14.336 --> 03:15.836
You're kidding.

03:15.838 --> 03:17.087
Check your stocking.

03:19.124 --> 03:22.459
So, listen, uh, I want to give
you a nice Christmas bonus.

03:22.461 --> 03:24.144
What do you think
would make you happy?

03:24.146 --> 03:27.264
Check your damn stocking
and put on the buckle.

03:28.766 --> 03:31.601
How about three weeks pay and
another kiss on the cheek?

03:31.603 --> 03:33.270
Do I get to pick
the cheek?

03:34.605 --> 03:36.773
Merry Christmas.

03:37.641 --> 03:40.243
Merry Christmas.

03:45.366 --> 03:48.702
Hey, Mom, where are you?

03:49.670 --> 03:53.173
Oh, okay,
that's about ten miles away...

03:53.175 --> 03:56.710
and it's rush hour,
so figure... three hours.

03:57.512 --> 04:00.180
Yeah, I can't wait
to see you, too.

04:00.182 --> 04:02.215
So I'm thinking that since

04:02.217 --> 04:04.217
this is our first Christmas
without Charlie,

04:04.219 --> 04:05.668
we should spend it together.

04:05.670 --> 04:10.006
Yes, Mom,
I'd rather get laid, too...

04:10.008 --> 04:12.442
but I think
family is more important.

04:12.444 --> 04:13.693
Hey, Mom.

04:13.695 --> 04:16.279
Yeah, I'm just driving
to Dad's.

04:16.281 --> 04:21.017
In 500 feet,
turn left.

04:21.019 --> 04:24.521
Yes, I'm seeing someone.

04:24.523 --> 04:26.490
No, you can't meet her.

04:26.492 --> 04:29.076
Because it's too soon.

04:29.078 --> 04:30.243
I don't know what it means.

04:30.245 --> 04:32.245
It's just
what she keeps telling me.

04:32.247 --> 04:33.747
Uh, Mom, y-you're breaking up.

04:33.749 --> 04:35.966
I-I'm sorry, what did you say?

04:36.801 --> 04:39.970
Y-Y-You want a tuna sandwich?

04:39.972 --> 04:44.207
Oh, oh, you're
in a two-man sandwich.

04:44.209 --> 04:49.146
Uh, well, I, I hope
they're using condiments.

04:49.148 --> 04:52.315
Uh, well, listen, I-I-I got
to go, I got another call.

04:52.317 --> 04:54.151
Dear Lord.

04:54.153 --> 04:55.519
Hello.

04:55.521 --> 04:57.404
Oh, Jake, merry Christmas.

04:57.406 --> 04:58.688
Hey, Dad,
I just wanted to call

04:58.690 --> 05:01.241
and tell you merry Christmas
and wish you happy holidays.

05:01.243 --> 05:03.226
No, no, Mom and Herb
are out to dinner.

05:03.228 --> 05:05.996
I'm just chilling
at the ski lodge.

05:05.998 --> 05:07.664
Room service.

05:07.666 --> 05:08.782
Oh, hang on.

05:08.784 --> 05:09.833
I ordered
a cheeseburger.

05:09.835 --> 05:11.034
Got to go, Dad.

05:11.036 --> 05:12.836
Yeah, I know
the tip's included.

05:12.838 --> 05:14.621
All right, bye.

05:14.623 --> 05:15.622
All right, now you call your mom

05:15.624 --> 05:17.541
and tell her
you're with your dad.

05:20.878 --> 05:24.747
Hey, Mom, I'm with your dad.

05:24.749 --> 05:25.849
No, no.

05:27.635 --> 05:29.686
♪ Men. ♪

05:29.688 --> 05:31.721
This is gonna be
the best Christmas ever.

05:31.723 --> 05:33.440
Yeah, swell.

05:33.442 --> 05:35.091
I got a great
new girlfriend.

05:35.093 --> 05:38.612
My girlfriend's got a
great new boyfriend.

05:38.614 --> 05:40.547
My mom is coming.

05:40.549 --> 05:43.733
So is mine.

05:45.586 --> 05:48.738
Wherever she is.

05:48.740 --> 05:49.956
Went to the Apple Store

05:49.958 --> 05:52.159
and bought myself
a bunch of cool presents.

05:52.161 --> 05:55.579
I went to the grocery store
and got myself an apple.

05:57.298 --> 06:00.500
Sounds like somebody's got
the holiday blues.

06:00.502 --> 06:01.668
Oh, little bit.

06:01.670 --> 06:03.503
My son's with his
mother and her husband,

06:03.505 --> 06:05.755
and this is my first Christmas
without Charlie.

06:05.757 --> 06:07.424
What would you two
normally do?

06:07.426 --> 06:09.426
Oh, we had kind of
a holiday tradition.

06:09.428 --> 06:11.961
Um, he would drink
a gallon of eggnog

06:11.963 --> 06:14.797
and then try to throw me
out of the house at gunpoint.

06:14.799 --> 06:16.983
Good times.

06:18.085 --> 06:20.320
Well, you're not going
to spend this year alone.

06:20.322 --> 06:22.939
You're going to have Christmas
with me and my mom.

06:22.941 --> 06:24.824
Well, thank you,
that's very nice of you.

06:24.826 --> 06:26.443
You want to hear a funny idea?

06:26.445 --> 06:28.111
You and my mom
are about the same age.

06:28.113 --> 06:30.197
If you guys started dating
and got married,

06:30.199 --> 06:32.165
you'd be my new daddy.

06:32.167 --> 06:35.252
Wait, h-hold on,
I-I'm your mom's age?

06:35.254 --> 06:36.836
How old do you think I am?

06:36.838 --> 06:39.289
I don't know, what, like 60?

06:39.291 --> 06:41.875
I'm 44.

06:41.877 --> 06:43.793
Oh, well, you look older.

06:45.797 --> 06:47.747
Oh, there she is.

06:47.749 --> 06:48.765
That's it.

06:48.767 --> 06:51.218
Tomorrow I start moisturizing.

06:52.270 --> 06:54.837
- Mom.
- Baby.

06:55.856 --> 06:57.440
Eyeball, eyeball.

06:57.442 --> 06:59.059
Nose and mouth.

06:59.061 --> 07:00.110
I love you north.

07:00.112 --> 07:01.061
I love you south.

07:03.348 --> 07:05.348
Hey, Alan, meet
my mother Robin.

07:05.350 --> 07:06.650
Nice to meet you, Alan.

07:06.652 --> 07:07.784
Likewise.

07:07.786 --> 07:09.452
Mom, let me show
you my place.

07:09.454 --> 07:12.205
Check it out, I
got my own ocean.

07:12.207 --> 07:13.790
Well, it's not
completely mine.

07:13.792 --> 07:15.825
I have to share the
other side with Japan.

07:15.827 --> 07:17.410
It's very nice, dear.

07:17.412 --> 07:19.746
Yeah, I'm rich.

07:19.748 --> 07:24.033
Well... I know
what I want for Christmas.

07:24.835 --> 07:27.470
♪ Men. ♪

07:27.472 --> 07:30.173
So how long have you two
been living together?

07:30.175 --> 07:32.392
A couple
of months.

07:32.394 --> 07:35.011
I see.

07:35.013 --> 07:36.930
I'm sorry, I-I have to ask.

07:36.932 --> 07:39.299
Is this the woman
you don't want me to meet?

07:41.002 --> 07:42.852
What?

07:42.854 --> 07:43.886
No.

07:43.888 --> 07:45.272
No, Alan is just a friend.

07:45.274 --> 07:46.489
Tell her.

07:46.491 --> 07:49.559
<i>Butch and Sundance,</i>
not <i>Brokeback Mountain.</i>

07:49.561 --> 07:51.227
Okay, sorry.

07:51.229 --> 07:53.530
I-I mean, you have to admit,
it's a rather strange set-up--

07:53.532 --> 07:57.033
a 33-year-old man living
with a 60-year-old.

07:58.402 --> 08:00.403
I'm 44.

08:00.405 --> 08:02.405
Right, me, too.

08:04.008 --> 08:05.675
Alan helped me through
my break-up with Bridget,

08:05.677 --> 08:07.010
and then he needed
a place to stay,

08:07.012 --> 08:09.078
so I asked him
to stick around.

08:09.080 --> 08:11.080
Oh, that is so like you.

08:12.100 --> 08:13.883
When Walden was
a little boy,

08:13.885 --> 08:17.554
he used to bring home sick,
helpless animals all the time.

08:19.357 --> 08:22.859
God help me,
I can't take that as an insult.

08:22.861 --> 08:24.927
So, uh, what do you do, Robin?

08:24.929 --> 08:25.862
I'm a primatologist.

08:25.864 --> 08:27.764
I, I work mainly
with gorillas.

08:27.766 --> 08:31.568
Oh, oh, so I guess that makes
you the gorilla my dreams.

08:35.239 --> 08:37.407
It was hysterical
when Bugs Bunny did it.

08:38.208 --> 08:40.327
And thanks
to the financial support

08:40.328 --> 08:41.711
of my brilliant son,
I have a private

08:41.712 --> 08:43.413
gorilla sanctuary in Temecula.

08:43.414 --> 08:44.164
Oh, no kidding?

08:44.166 --> 08:45.298
Yeah, we take
gorillas

08:45.300 --> 08:46.466
who were born
in captivity

08:46.468 --> 08:48.218
and those who have lost
their wild habitats

08:48.220 --> 08:50.119
and provide them
with a safe, stable,

08:50.121 --> 08:51.788
loving family
environment.

08:51.790 --> 08:53.790
Oh, that sounds wonderful.

08:53.792 --> 08:57.060
Does one have to be a gorilla
to apply for admittance?

08:57.062 --> 08:58.345
I'm afraid so.

08:58.347 --> 09:00.313
Story of my life.

09:00.315 --> 09:01.481
When I was little,
I always wanted

09:01.483 --> 09:02.682
to play with the gorillas.

09:02.684 --> 09:05.568
I even made up my own
imaginary gorilla friend.

09:05.570 --> 09:06.936
Remember Magilla, Mom?

09:06.938 --> 09:09.639
Hmm, yeah,
but he wasn't imaginary.

09:09.641 --> 09:11.608
What?

09:11.610 --> 09:13.309
Walden, Magilla lived
with us

09:13.311 --> 09:15.528
for the first four years
of your life.

09:16.364 --> 09:17.947
He was real?

09:19.283 --> 09:20.367
Yeah.

09:20.369 --> 09:21.818
Do you want
to see some pictures?

09:21.820 --> 09:25.988
Wait, w-w-wait,
Magilla was real?

09:25.990 --> 09:27.424
Very much so.

09:27.426 --> 09:29.542
Wait, you actually had
a gorilla living with you?

09:29.544 --> 09:32.679
Yep, I was doing experiments
to see if gorillas could learn

09:32.681 --> 09:34.214
as fast as human children, so

09:34.216 --> 09:36.766
I raised Magilla and Walden
together from birth.

09:36.768 --> 09:38.802
Wow.

09:38.804 --> 09:42.222
All we had was a schnauzer
and an Argentinean tennis pro.

09:44.075 --> 09:47.227
Uncle Javier.

09:48.145 --> 09:50.613
The tennis pro,
not the schnauzer.

09:50.615 --> 09:55.017
Hold on a second,
I was raised with a gorilla?

09:55.019 --> 09:57.654
Oh, well, just until
you started preschool.

09:57.656 --> 10:01.157
Now, look, here's you and
Magilla together in your crib.

10:05.262 --> 10:06.496
And here's

10:06.498 --> 10:08.948
the two of you
at your first birthday.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.901
Wait a minute,

10:11.903 --> 10:14.704
is that how I learned
sign language?

10:14.706 --> 10:17.006
I'm sorry, I don't have
any bananas.

10:17.008 --> 10:18.875
Look, there's
the two of you

10:18.877 --> 10:21.361
on the playground.

10:21.363 --> 10:22.645
Oh, your first
Halloween.

10:23.481 --> 10:25.498
You went as a gorilla,

10:25.500 --> 10:26.933
and Magilla went as a ghost.

10:29.954 --> 10:31.921
Whoa, whoa.

10:31.923 --> 10:34.574
Yeah, okay. Yeah, it's
starting to come back to me.

10:34.576 --> 10:35.825
Like, riding
tricycles together,

10:35.827 --> 10:38.060
and running...
running around the house.

10:38.062 --> 10:40.613
Or playing hide in the closet.

10:40.615 --> 10:43.500
Wait. Why were we always
hiding in the closet?

10:43.502 --> 10:46.369
Well, the Homeowners Association
didn't allow cats or dogs.

10:46.371 --> 10:48.621
What would they have said
about a gorilla?

10:48.623 --> 10:50.623
Yeah. I remember.

10:50.625 --> 10:52.542
You told me he was my brother.

10:52.544 --> 10:54.878
Well, in a sense, he was.

10:54.880 --> 10:57.046
And then one day, he was gone.

10:57.048 --> 10:59.081
Yeah.

10:59.083 --> 11:01.184
You said
he got sent back to the jungle.

11:01.186 --> 11:02.919
Well, sweetheart,
we didn't have any choice.

11:02.921 --> 11:04.637
He was getting too big.
He, uh...

11:04.639 --> 11:06.923
He tried
to kill a Jehovah's Witness.

11:08.826 --> 11:11.260
Now, Now, to be fair,
who among us hasn't...

11:11.262 --> 11:12.529
Not now, Alan.

11:14.264 --> 11:16.199
This is really starting
to freak me out.

11:16.201 --> 11:17.367
Well, sweetie,
I-I don't understand

11:17.369 --> 11:19.702
why you're making such
a big deal out of this.

11:19.704 --> 11:21.621
You're kidding, right?

11:21.623 --> 11:24.958
I-I just discovered
that my brother is a gorilla!

11:24.960 --> 11:27.327
That's-That's
kind of a big deal!

11:27.329 --> 11:29.045
Hey, my brother was a pig,
so, I mean...

11:29.047 --> 11:31.280
I said, not now, Alan!

11:32.333 --> 11:34.250
Walden, calm down.

11:34.252 --> 11:37.453
You do realize
that I spent my entire childhood

11:37.455 --> 11:38.805
worrying that if I misbehaved,

11:38.807 --> 11:41.508
I would get sent away
to the jungle like Magilla!

11:41.510 --> 11:44.110
One false move, Zimbabwe!

11:44.112 --> 11:46.128
Well, sweetheart, I...

11:46.130 --> 11:48.314
I never knew
that you felt like that.

11:48.316 --> 11:49.632
Of course you didn't.

11:49.634 --> 11:52.018
You were so busy
doing your experiment!

11:52.887 --> 11:54.988
Walden!

11:56.875 --> 11:59.025
Kids, huh?

11:59.027 --> 12:00.443
So, you seeing anybody?

12:00.445 --> 12:02.662
♪ Men. ♪

12:04.867 --> 12:06.617
♪ Men. ♪

12:06.619 --> 12:08.786
Walden, it's Mom.
Where are you?

12:08.788 --> 12:11.372
Please call me back
so we can talk about this.

12:11.374 --> 12:15.743
I had no idea he'd repressed
all those childhood memories.

12:15.745 --> 12:17.128
Well, apparently,

12:17.130 --> 12:19.530
losing what he thought was
his sibling was very traumatic.

12:19.532 --> 12:22.967
I'm wondering if maybe I have
to rethink his Christmas gift.

12:22.969 --> 12:24.702
Why? What did you get him?

12:24.704 --> 12:27.204
A bathrobe.

12:27.206 --> 12:28.973
Yeah, not a good idea.

12:28.975 --> 12:30.708
And I can't even return it.

12:30.710 --> 12:33.377
It's slightly irregular.

12:33.379 --> 12:35.880
You must think
I'm a terrible mother.

12:35.882 --> 12:39.550
Well, let's compare
mothering techniques.

12:39.552 --> 12:41.602
Um, did you tell him
that Disneyland burned down

12:41.604 --> 12:43.187
to avoid having
to take him there

12:43.189 --> 12:44.822
for his sixth, seventh
and eighth birthdays?

12:44.824 --> 12:46.023
No.

12:46.025 --> 12:47.725
Did you tell him
to walk it off

12:47.727 --> 12:48.893
after his appendix burst?

12:48.895 --> 12:50.561
No.

12:50.563 --> 12:52.580
Did you tell me
the only reason you got pregnant

12:52.582 --> 12:54.448
was because you didn't want
to smear your lipstick?

12:54.450 --> 12:57.752
Of course not!

12:57.754 --> 12:59.337
Then, far as I'm concerned,

12:59.339 --> 13:01.906
you're Mother
of the Freakin' Year. Hmm.

13:01.908 --> 13:03.875
Mm. Although I did store
Walden's embryo

13:03.877 --> 13:06.294
in a cryogenic chamber until
Magilla's mother got pregnant

13:06.296 --> 13:08.746
so they could be born
at the same time.

13:08.748 --> 13:11.516
Okay, flag on the play.

13:11.518 --> 13:13.050
You did what?

13:13.052 --> 13:15.102
I needed my child
and the gorilla

13:15.104 --> 13:17.805
to be born at the same time
for the experiment to be valid.

13:17.807 --> 13:19.607
And your husband
was okay with this?

13:19.609 --> 13:21.726
It was for science.

13:21.728 --> 13:23.928
And I may not have told him.

13:23.930 --> 13:27.064
Okay, well, well, after all
that time and energy,

13:27.066 --> 13:28.482
what did you learn?

13:28.484 --> 13:31.452
My son is smarter
than a gorilla.

13:31.454 --> 13:34.438
Mine's not.

13:34.440 --> 13:37.959
♪ Men. ♪

13:44.583 --> 13:46.634
Oh, Walden,
what are you doing here?

13:46.636 --> 13:49.453
My brother is a gorilla,
and she sent him away.

13:49.455 --> 13:53.424
I'm sorry. Is that some sort
of American <i>Christmas Carol?</i>

13:53.426 --> 13:55.593
No. It's a succinct summation

13:55.595 --> 13:59.013
of my seminal years
with a simian sibling.

13:59.015 --> 14:01.199
Are you drunk?

14:01.201 --> 14:03.818
I ought to be.
I've taken the necessary steps.

14:04.937 --> 14:07.071
Sweetie, this isn't
a very good time.

14:07.073 --> 14:08.439
You're telling me.

14:08.441 --> 14:10.024
My mother is a mad scientist,

14:10.026 --> 14:12.577
and I spent the first four years
of my life

14:12.579 --> 14:15.780
